o expect from an observational point of view\nin terms of frequency range of excited modes, and investigate the behavior of\nthe instabilities with stellar evolution and increasing degree of the mode.\nFurthermore, our pulsational stability analysis, once compared to the empirical\nresults of Sim\\'on-D\\'iaz et al. (2016), indicates that stellar oscillations\noriginated by a heat mechanism can not explain alone the occurrence of the\nlarge non-rotational line-broadening component commonly detected in the O star\nand B supergiant domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Aug 2016 07:59:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-21"}
