es of interest, our result restricts\nthe possible values of the Rokhlin dimension to $0, 1$ and $\\infty$, showing a\nstriking parallel to the behavior of the nuclear dimension for simple\nC*-algebras. We also show that an action of a finite group with finite Rokhlin\ndimension with commuting towers automatically has the Rokhlin property if the\nalgebra is UHF-absorbing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Aug 2016 08:35:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Feb 2017 15:58:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 30 Mar 2018 09:57:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-02"}
